  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean house windows?",
  "response": "Cleaning house windows effectively can enhance your home's appearance and let in more light. Here\u2019s a comprehensive guide to help you clean your windows thoroughly:\n\n### Materials Needed\n- Bucket\n- Squeegee\n- Soft cloths or microfiber towels\n- Window cleaning solution (commercial or homemade)\n- Scraper (for stuck-on debris)\n- Sponge or scrub brush\n- Ladder (if needed for upper windows)\n- Gloves (optional)\n\n### Homemade Window Cleaning Solution\nYou can make an effective cleaning solution with common household items:\n- **Vinegar Solution**: Mix equal parts of white vinegar and water in a spray bottle.\n- **Dish Soap Solution**: Add a few drops of dish soap to a bucket of warm water.\n\n### Steps to Clean Windows\n\n1. **Remove Dust and Dirt**: \n   - Start by dusting the window frames and sills with a dry cloth or a duster to remove any loose dirt and cobwebs.\n\n2. **Prepare Your Cleaning Solution**: \n   - If using a homemade solution, mix it in a spray bottle or bucket.\n\n3. **Wet the Window**: \n   - Use a sponge or scrub brush to apply the cleaning solution to the window. Make sure to cover the entire surface.\n\n4. **Scrape Off Stuck-On Debris**: \n   - If there are any stubborn spots, use a scraper to gently remove them without scratching the glass.\n\n5. **Squeegee the Window**: \n   - Starting at the top corner, pull the squeegee down in a straight line. Wipe the blade with a clean cloth after each stroke to avoid streaks.\n   - You can also use a horizontal motion, but make sure to wipe the squeegee after each pass.\n\n6. **Dry the Edges**: \n   - Use a clean, dry cloth to wipe the edges of the window and the sill to catch any drips.\n\n7. **Repeat as Necessary**: \n   - If the windows are particularly dirty, you may need to repeat the process.\n\n8. **Clean Window Screens (if applicable)**: \n   - Remove screens and wash them with a mild soap solution. Rinse and let them dry before reattaching.\n\n### Tips\n- **Choose the Right Day**: Clean windows on a cloudy day to prevent the cleaning solution from drying too quickly, which can cause streaks.\n- **Use the Right Tools**: Consider using a professional-grade squeegee for better results.\n- **Safety First**: If using a ladder, ensure it is stable, and never overreach. It might be safer to hire a professional for high windows.\n\nBy following these steps, you can achieve clear, streak-free windows that brighten up your home!",
